title.narrative: Twiyubake - Improved Services for Vulnerable Populations (ISVP)

description.narrative: (Rwanda): .USAID's.Twiyubake (Let's Build Ourselves) activity enhances households' capacity to mitigate.the impact of social and economic shocks and improve health. Twiyubake.teaches communities a range of skills related to health, nutrition, food.security, preventing gender-based violence, technical vocational education and.training (TVET), business development support, and social services. With FY 2019 funding, USAID will extend the Twiyubake.activity from February 22, 2020 to September 22, 2020 to provide TVET.scholarships, materials for Early Childhood Development intervention, and.conditional household grants. In order to increase income and dietary.diversity, Twiyubake will establish Farmer Field Schools, and provide inputs.and nutrition trainings. Twiyubake will.conduct social behavior change communication campaigns to promote pre and.post-natal care, facility delivery, optimal birth spacing and reproductive.health, and water, sanitation, and hygiene (WASH) practices including hand.washing, safe water use, and latrine cleanliness to prevent diarrheal diseases.for improved maternal and child health... ..USAID's.Twiyubake (Let's Build Ourselves) activity is implemented by Global.Communities, an organization with proven expertise supporting Rwanda's most.vulnerable populations - orphans and vulnerable children (OVC), people living.with HIV/AIDS, and their families. Twiyubake provides comprehensive support to.vulnerable families across 12 districts of Rwanda. .. ..Twiyubake.directly contributes to the Integrated Country Strategy objective 3.1 to.improve the health and nutritional status of Rwandans, and thereby Mission Goal.3, to promote inclusive country-led development..
